@startuml stripe-webhook-subscription-sync
title Stripe Webhook Subscription Sync
hide footbox
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontSize 16
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #111111
  LifeLineBorderColor #111111
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantBorderColor #111111
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ActorBorderColor #111111
  ActorBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  GroupBorderColor #111111
  GroupBackgroundColor #EEEEEE
}

actor "Stripe" as Stripe
participant "Webhook Route\nRaw Body" as Route
participant "Billing\nController" as Controller
participant "Webhook\nService" as WebhookService
participant "Stripe Billing\nProvider" as Provider
participant "Webhook Event\nModel" as EventModel
participant "Billing Queue\nRuntime" as Queue
participant "Billing Sync\nWorker/Service" as SyncService
participant "Subscription +\nEntitlement Models" as Models

== 1. Receive webhook ==
Stripe -> Route: POST /api/billing/webhooks/stripe
Route -> Controller: raw application/json body\n+ stripe-signature
Controller -> WebhookService: acceptStripeWebhookEvent()

== 2. Verify and dedupe event ==
WebhookService -> Provider: verify Stripe signature
Provider --> WebhookService: verified event
WebhookService -> EventModel: persist by provider + eventId\nwith payload hash
alt Duplicate event
  EventModel --> WebhookService: existing webhook event
  WebhookService --> Stripe: accepted duplicate response
else New event
  EventModel --> WebhookService: pending webhook event
  WebhookService -> Queue: enqueue processing job
  WebhookService --> Stripe: accepted + queued flag
end

== 3. Resolve subscription/customer ==
Queue -> SyncService: processBillingWebhookEventById()
SyncService -> EventModel: load pending event
SyncService -> Models: resolve workspace from metadata,\nsubscription, or customer
SyncService -> Models: ensure subscription foundation

== 4. Apply subscription status ==
alt Active/success lifecycle
  SyncService -> Provider: retrieve/list Stripe subscription\nwhen payload needs sync
  SyncService -> Models: map plan/add-ons,\nstatus active/trialing
  SyncService -> Models: recompute entitlements
else Failure/status-change lifecycle
  SyncService -> Models: apply past_due/canceled/\nincomplete lifecycle fields
  SyncService -> Models: recompute entitlement flags
end
SyncService -> EventModel: mark processed or failed

== 5. Return webhook acknowledgement ==
note over WebhookService,SyncService
The HTTP request acknowledges persistence/enqueueing.
Subscription state is applied by the worker or replay processor.
end note

@enduml
